      MultiTreeMap MultiTreeMap.clear​(java.lang.String name)
      Removes all values associated with a name but does not remove the name from the set, so it stays in the same position as it was added.
      MultiTreeMap MultiTreeMap.copyDeep()
      Creates a deep copy of this MultiTreeMap, by creating a new instance with the same parings and in the same order as the original; new, identical lists are created for the simple keys, the tree keys, and the singleton keys.
      MultiTreeMap MultiTreeMap.copyNameFrom​(MultiTreeMap from, java.lang.String name)
      Adds to this tree the contents associated with the specified name in the from tree, with exactly the same type of key (singleton / hierarchical).
      protected MultiTreeMap MultiTreeMap.copyNameFrom​(MultiTreeMap from, java.lang.String name, boolean deepCopy)
      Handles the functionality of copyNameFrom(MultiTreeMap, String) and copyNameFromDeep(MultiTreeMap, String).
      MultiTreeMap MultiTreeMap.copyNameFromDeep​(MultiTreeMap from, java.lang.String name)
      Adds to this tree the contents associated with the specified name in the from tree, with exactly the same type of key (singleton / hierarchical).
      MultiTreeMap MultiTreeMap.copyShallow()
      Creates a shallow copy of this MultiTreeMap, by creating a new instance with the same parings (an identical backing map) and in the same order as the original; new, identical lists are created for the simple keys, the tree keys, and the singleton keys.
